Perfect! I have all the information you need. Here's a comprehensive report on the real-time presence system in SynergY:

## 1. Socket.IO Event Handlers (server/index.js, lines 490-499)

```javascript
io.on('connection', (socket) => {
  socket.on('join_room', (roomId) => socket.join(roomId));
  socket.on('join_user', (userId) => socket.join(`user_${userId}`));
  socket.on('leave_room', (roomId) => socket.leave(roomId));
  socket.on('typing', ({ roomId, userName }) => {
    socket.to(roomId).emit('user_typing', { userName });
  });
});
```

**Socket Events Emitted by Server:**
- `member_joined` (line 136): `{ user_id, user_name, user_color }`
- `member_removed` (line 169): `{ user_id }`
- `user_typing` (line 497): `{ userName }`
- `new_chat_message` (line 459)
- `new_contribution` (line 221)
- `room_updated` (line 90)
- `notification` (line 30)

---

## 2. Client-Side Socket Setup (Room.jsx, lines 45-152)

**Socket Connection & Room/User Joining:**
```javascript
const socketRef = useRef(null);
const userRef = useRef(user);
useEffect(() => { userRef.current = user; }, [user]);

useEffect(() => {
  const socket = io({ transports: ['websocket', 'polling'] });
  socketRef.current = socket;

  socket.on('connect', () => {
    socket.emit('join_room', roomId);
    if (user) socket.emit('join_user', user.id);
  });
```

**Member Joined Listener (lines 95-100):**
```javascript
socket.on('member_joined', (member) => {
  setMembers(prev => {
    if (prev.find(m => m.user_id === member.user_id)) return prev;
    return [...prev, { ...member, contribution_count: 0, joined_at: Date.now() }];
  });
});
```

**Member Removed Listener (lines 102-110):**
```javascript
socket.on('member_removed', ({ user_id: removedId }) => {
  setMembers(prev => prev.map(m =>
    m.user_id === removedId ? { ...m, removed_at: Date.now() } : m
  ));
  // Check against the current user — use a ref so we don't capture stale user
  if (userRef.current?.id === removedId) {
    setMembershipStatus('removed');
  }
});
```

**Typing Users State & Listener (lines 30, 133-139):**
```javascript
const [typingUsers, setTypingUsers] = useState([]);

socket.on('user_typing', ({ userName }) => {
  setTypingUsers(prev => prev.includes(userName) ? prev : [...prev, userName]);
  clearTimeout(typingTimerRef.current[userName]);
  typingTimerRef.current[userName] = setTimeout(() => {
    setTypingUsers(prev => prev.filter(u => u !== userName));
  }, 3000);
});
```

---

## 3. Room Header JSX (lines 516-591)

**Header Structure:**
```javascript
<header className="room-header">
  <div className="room-header-left">
    <button className="btn-icon" onClick={() => navigate('/')} title="Home">
      ←
    </button>
    <div className="room-title-wrap">
      <h1 className="room-title">{room?.title || 'Untitled Room'}</h1>
      {!!room?.is_entry_locked && <span className="badge badge-locked">🚪 Closed</span>}
      {!!room?.is_locked && <span className="badge badge-locked">✏️ Locked</span>}
    </div>
  </div>

  <div className="room-header-right">
    {/* View toggles: Collab, Review, Document */}
    <div className="view-toggle">
      <button className={`toggle-btn ${view === 'collab' ? 'active' : ''}`}
        onClick={() => setView('collab')}>Collab</button>
      <button className={`toggle-btn ${view === 'review' ? 'active' : ''}`}
        onClick={() => setView('review')}>Review</button>
      <button className={`toggle-btn ${view === 'document' ? 'active' : ''}`}
        onClick={() => setView('document')}>Document</button>
    </div>

    {/* Share Button */}
    <button className="btn btn-secondary" onClick={handleCopyLink}>
      {linkCopied ? '✓ Copied!' : '🔗 Share'}
    </button>

    {/* Export Button */}
    <button className="btn btn-secondary" onClick={handleExport} 
      title="Download as .txt">↓ Export</button>

    {/* Contributors Button — shows member count */}
    <button className="btn btn-secondary contributors-btn"
      onClick={() => setShowContributors(true)}
      title="View contributors">
      👥 {members.filter(m => !m.removed_at).length}
    </button>

    {/* Lock Controls (creator only) */}
    {isCreator && (
      <>
        <button className={`btn lock-btn ${room?.is_entry_locked ? 'lock-btn--active' : ''}`}
          onClick={handleEntryLockToggle}
          title={room?.is_entry_locked ? 'Entry locked — click to open' : 'Entry open — click to lock'}>
          {room?.is_entry_locked ? '🚪 Closed' : '🚪 Open'}
        </button>
        <button className={`btn lock-btn ${room?.is_locked ? 'lock-btn--active' : ''}`}
          onClick={handleContribLockToggle}
          title={room?.is_locked ? 'Posts locked — click to unlock' : 'Posts open — click to lock'}>
          {room?.is_locked ? '✏️ Locked' : '✏️ Posts'}
        </button>
      </>
    )}

    {/* Theme toggle */}
    <button className="btn-icon" onClick={toggleTheme} title="Toggle theme">
      {theme === 'light' ? '🌙' : '☀️'}
    </button>

    {/* Notification bell */}
    <NotificationBell notifications={notifications} onMarkAllRead={markAllNotificationsRead} />
  </div>
</header>
```

---

## 4. Member/User Data Available on Client

**Members State (initialized on component load, lines 194-196):**
```javascript
const [members, setMembers] = useState([]);

// Loaded from GET /api/rooms/:id/members
// Each member object shape:
{
  id: string,                    // UUID
  room_id: string,              // Room ID
  user_id: string,              // User ID
  user_name: string,            // User's display name
  user_color: string,           // Hex color (e.g., '#6366f1')
  joined_at: number,            // Timestamp
  last_seen: number,            // Timestamp
  removed_at: number | null,    // Timestamp if removed
  removed_by: string | null,    // User ID who removed them
  contribution_count: number    // Count of contributions
}
```

**Current User Object (from useUser() context, lines 16, 42):**
```javascript
const { user, login, theme, toggleTheme } = useUser();

// user object shape:
{
  id: string,              // UUID
  name: string,            // Display name
  color: string,           // Hex color (e.g., '#6366f1')
  // potentially created_at: number
}
```

**Typing Users State (line 30):**
```javascript
const [typingUsers, setTypingUsers] = useState([]);
// Array of user names currently typing
```

**Member Count Display (line 562):**
```javascript
{members.filter(m => !m.removed_at).length}
// Shows active (non-removed) members only
```

